# Copy to .env — never commit real secrets.
#
# Planning page (/planning): password gate + server-backed storage.
#
# --- Recommended (works on Netlify + local): Supabase Postgres ---
# 1. Create a free project at https://supabase.com
# 2. SQL Editor → paste contents of database/supabase-planning.sql → Run
# 3. Project Settings → API → copy Project URL + service_role key (secret)
# 4. Set these only on the server (Netlify env + local .env):
#
# SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxx.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJI...
# Same keys sometimes appear as NUXT_SUPABASE_URL / NUXT_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY — both are accepted server-side.
#
# Never expose SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY to the browser or NUXT_PUBLIC_*.

# --- Netlify Blobs (only if you skip Supabase) ---
# Nitro's Netlify Function often does NOT receive NETLIFY_BLOBS_CONTEXT; without it, Blobs calls fail and saves never stick.
# Fix: add a Personal Access Token (User settings → Applications → Personal access tokens) with Blobs permissions:
#
# NETLIFY_AUTH_TOKEN=nfp_xxxxxxxx
#
# SITE_ID is injected automatically for Functions — do not paste it unless debugging.
# Optional override: NETLIFY_BLOB_SITE_ID=...

# --- Planner login (same as before) ---
# If the session secret contains & ? ^ * ! etc., wrap it in double quotes:
# NUXT_PLANNING_SESSION_SECRET="your-secret-here"

# Optional: force planner storage backend for local `nuxt preview` etc.
# PLANNING_STORAGE_FS=1  → .data/planning-state.json (when Supabase not configured)
# Netlify: names must match exactly (NUXT_ prefix). Under Site settings → Environment variables,
# scope both to Builds, Functions, and Runtime so API routes receive them.
#
# If login returns 503 on Netlify, also try duplicate keys without NUXT_ (same values):
# PLANNING_PASSWORD / PLANNING_SESSION_SECRET — some builds only expose non-prefixed vars.
#
# Temporary troubleshooting (Function logs): PLANNING_AUTH_DEBUG=1

NUXT_PLANNING_PASSWORD=YourPlanningPasswordHere
NUXT_PLANNING_SESSION_SECRET="UseAtLeast32RandomCharsForSigningCookies"
